# Browser compatibility targets
# Read by: @tailwindcss/vite (Lightning CSS), postcss-preset-env, browserslist tooling
#
# WHY these specific minimums:
#   chrome >= 100  → Chrome 100-110 lacks oklch → Lightning CSS generates hex fallbacks
#                    Chrome 100+ uses text-size-adjust (no -webkit prefix)
#   firefox >= 102 → Firefox 102-112 lacks oklch → hex fallbacks generated
#   safari >= 15.4 → Uses -webkit-text-size-adjust; oklch added in Safari 15.4
#   edge >= 100    → Edge 100-110 lacks oklch → hex fallbacks generated
#
# Result: Lightning CSS will emit hex fallbacks BEFORE oklch() values in the build,
# resolving the Microsoft Edge Tools "not supported by Chrome < 111" warnings.

chrome >= 100
firefox >= 102
safari >= 15.4
ios_saf >= 15.4
edge >= 100
samsung >= 17

not dead
not ie > 0
